Program statements
* Calculate pre-sum - this keeps a running sum (or snapshot) of the frequency array for each character at position 'i' in the input string.
* Iterate each query. 
* If k >=13, add true to result. Iteration step is done. The upperBound of oddCount is 26 so the threshold condition would always be true with 2*k (2 x 13 = 26). 
* If k <13, continue with iteration. Count the number of characters that occur an odd number of times over the given span. If this count falls below threshold, add true to the result, otherwise add false.

**Threshold**: an odd number of characters in the span gets one odd character for free so the threshold is 2*k + 1

```
      public List<Boolean> canMakePaliQueries(String s, int[][] queries) {
        var N = s.length();
        var f = new int[N + 1][26];
        for(int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
            f[i] = Arrays.copyOf(f[i - 1], 26);         
            f[i][s.charAt(i - 1) - 'a']++; 
        }

        var result = new LinkedList<Boolean>();
        for(var query : queries) {
            var x = query[0];
            var y = query[1];
            var k = query[2];
            var b = true;
            if(k < 13) {
                var oddCount = 0;
                for(int i = 0; i < 26; i++) {
                    var z = (f[y + 1][i] - f[x][i]) & 1;
                    if(z != 0) oddCount++;                        
                }    
                var span = y - x + 1;
                var threshold = (span & 1) == 0 ? 2*k : 2*k + 1;
                b = oddCount <= threshold;         
            } 
            result.add(b); 
        }
        return result;
    }

