solutions.content:
Since we can rearrange all characters in substring, **we only need to consider the parity of the occurence of each character in substring**, and this is the essential point of why we can use bitmask for info storage.

By preprocessing the parity of occurence by using a integer to store the state - `0` for even and `1` for odd, we can easily get the parity of any substring using `XOR` command.

Further, one more case is the parity of the length of the substring,
* if `len(substr)` is odd, we can put one extra single character at the center of the substring while it's still palindrome
* if `len(substr)` is even, then only paired characters are accepted

We count all single characters (minus one when length is odd), and calling it `cnt`. Now, we only need to change half of them on one side to match with the corresponding character on the other side, so push `true` when `k` is greater than `cnt /  2` in even case and `(cnt - 1) / 2` in odd case, then false otherwise, which should be the final correct result
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<bool> canMakePaliQueries(string s, vector<vector<int>>& queries) {
        vector<unsigned int> bitPre(s.size(), 0); 
        for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) { // only need to record parity of each character using XOR
            int idx = s[i] - 'a';
            if (i == 0) bitPre[i] = 1 << idx;
            else bitPre[i] = bitPre[i - 1] ^ (1 << idx);
        }
        vector<bool> res;
        for (auto &q: queries) {
            int l = q[0], r = q[1], k = q[2];
            unsigned int bits = bitPre[r];
            if (l > 0) bits ^= bitPre[l - 1]; 
            if ((l - r + 1) % 2 == 0) { // check length parity
                int cnt = __builtin_popcount(bits); // count number of 1 inside bits
                res.push_back(cnt / 2 <= k);
            } else {
                int cnt = __builtin_popcount(bits); // count number of 1 inside bits
                res.push_back((cnt - 1) / 2 <= k);
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

