   'f'    0 0 0 0 0 0
   ......[no other characters in this example, will be all 0]
   'z'   0 0 0 0 0 0

 for query [0,3,1], we only want to know the number of extra character that we add in index 1,2,3,4, so we just need to check (dp[4][i] - dp[0][i]) %2 for all characters i: 
 (1-0)%2 + (1-0) %2+ (1-0)%2 + (1-0) %2 + ... + (0-0) %2 = 4

 since 4/2=2>1, so [0,3,1] is false

