Store the counts of each variable for each each index.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Make a vector of size 26 to store the count of each alphabet for each index of string s uisng a hashmap.Then using the concepts of prefix sum you can check the count of all alphabets for any range from 0 to s.size().Then just check the alphabets who have count as odd number.Now if we add or substract one from any odd number it becomes even.Lets understand by example : The number of a's are 3 and number of b's are 5, now if we convert any of these three a's to b then the count of a becomes 2 and that of b becomes 6, and rearrenging them we can make a palindrome.
