Idea is Simple :
	1. calculate the count of all the previous characters and keep it in some place.
	2. Once queries comes, the find all the diff between count of characters for left -1 position and right position
	3. We can remove pairs of characters if both are same, so only consider remaining characters
	4. Then check if substring is even or odd if odd, then we can have one distinct character so remove one from difference
	5. then divide it into two parts and we will try to make first half same as second 
	6. So If first half count is less than or equal to k then it should be true
	7. 
```
class Solution {
    public List<Boolean> canMakePaliQueries(String s, int[][] queries) {
        HashMap<Integer,int[]> map = new HashMap<>();

        int[] arr = new int[26];
        map.put(-1, new int[26]);
        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++) {
            char c = s.charAt(i);
            arr[c-'a']++;
            map.put(i, getArray(arr));
        }

        List<Boolean> list = new ArrayList<>();
        for(int[] query : queries) {
            int diff = 0;
            int left = query[0];
            int right = query[1];
            int k = query[2];
            for(int i=0; i<26; i++) {
                diff += (map.get(right)[i] - map.get(left-1)[i])%2;
            }
            int count = right - left + 1;
            if(count%2==0) {
                list.add(diff/2 <= k);
            }
            else{
                list.add((diff-1)/2 <= k);
            }
        }

        return list;
    }

    public int[] getArray(int[] arr) {
        int[] temp = new int[26];
        for(int i=0; i<26; i++) {
            temp[i] = arr[i];
        }

        return temp;
    }
}
