since we can rearrange substring , we have to check freq of every character and see if we can somehow arrange those characters to make a palindrome

# Approach
if freq of every element is even , we can make that substring as palindrome.
if freq of all element is even except one, we can still make it palindrome..

we count number of letters with odd freq [ as they can create problem]
in one operation we can make 2 characters same [by making one equal to other]

suppose we have frequencies like this
a->11
b->13
c->9
d->15
e->14

now we have to find which characters are creating problem
a->1 ( one character of a might create problem)
b->1 ( one character of b might create problem)
c->1 ( one character of c might create problem)
d->1 ( one character of d might create problem)
e->0 ( zero character of e might create problem) // we dont have to consider this case as it can always make a palindrome.

now we have 4 characters [a,b,c,d] which will create problem.
in one operation we can change any character to any!
lets say if k>0 then we change problematic occurence of a to b
now since we have changed one occurence of a to b, b becomes even in nature thus there are no problematic occurences of b in the array now.

so in one operation we can somehow adjust 2 characters.
and in the end we can have atmax 1 problematic character, which we can plate in the middle of string



