solutions.content:
// General Bit operations
// & operator - & operator (operates on 2 bitmasks) returns the new bitmask that contains only those bits set as 1 which are 1 in both bitmasks
// m << i => shift each bit of 'm' to left 'i' times (1 << i means shift 1 to left 'i' times -> this would basically SET 'ith' bit as 1)
// mask = mask | 1 << i (this will SET the 'ith' bit in 'mask' as 1)
// mask - 1 -> eliminates the LAST SUBSEQUENT bit (meaning, the last bit which is 1 will be removed -> this is used to find other subset)
// (submask - 1) & mask -> gives ALL the SUBSETs of mask one by one

// TC : O(M*N + P*2^7); M = words.length, N = words[0].length, P = puzzles.length, puzzle[0],length = max(7) so number of subsets that could be made is (2 ^ 7) - 1
// SC : O(M); if M different masks could be formed
```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> findNumOfValidWords(String[] words, String[] puzzles) {

        Map<Integer, Integer> mapOfBitmask = new HashMap<>(); // map contains the bitmasked string and their frequency

        for(String word : words){
            int maskWord = 0; // this butmask would tell that which all characters are there in the word 
            for(int i = 0; i < word.length(); i++){
                maskWord |= 1 << (word.charAt(i) - 'a'); // set 'ith' char(bit in bitmask) as 1
            }
            mapOfBitmask.put(maskWord, mapOfBitmask.getOrDefault(maskWord, 0) + 1);
        }

        List<Integer> res = new ArrayList<>();

        for(String puzzle : puzzles) { // puzzle = bde (b, d, e) -> its subsets are -> {b}, {d}, {e}, {b, d}, {b, e}, {d, e}, {} -> total = (2 ^ n) - 1 = 8 - 1 = 7 where n = len(bde)
            int puzzleMask = 0; // this butmask would tell that which all characters are there in the puzzle 
            for(int i = 0; i < puzzle.length(); i++){
                puzzleMask |= 1 << (puzzle.charAt(i) - 'a');  // set 'ith' char (bit in bitmask) as 1
            }

            int count = 0;
            int subMask = puzzleMask; // if mask represents the SET of characters then subMask is the SUBSET of the characters in SET
            int first = 1 << (puzzle.charAt(0) - 'a'); // first is a bitmask which which only have 0th idx char to be set as 1

            // this while be out of loop after it checks ALL the subsets of puzzle and it finally sees the empty subset
            while(true) {
                // (subMask & first) == first -> subMask & first will ONLY be equals to first if and only if the 'ith' bit in subMask and first is set as 1 because all other bits in first are set as 0 so '&' will make every other bit as 0
                // if map contains the subset, then add it to answer
                if((subMask & first) == first && mapOfBitmask.containsKey(subMask)){
                    count += mapOfBitmask.get(subMask);
                }

                if(subMask == 0) break; // if submask is 0, it means subset is empty so break out (submask will become 0 AFTER we tried all the subsets)

                // once we find out if the subset of chars (submask) is present in map or not, it is time to try other subset (submask)
                // subMask - 1 eliminates the LAST bit and (& mask) will make sure that after eliminating the LAST significant bit from submask the new submask will ONLY contains the bits which are set to 1 in mask (this means that '& mask' will make sure that chars in new subset will only come from original set)
                // for ex: p = bdeg => 0101101 = mask
                // subMask - 1 = 0101101 - 0000001 = 0101100 => bde (bde is a subset of bdeg)
                // 0101100 & 0101101 = 0101100
                // Now sub = 0101100 => bde (subset of bdeg)
                // sub - 1 = 0101100 - 0000001 = 0101010
                // 0101010 & 0101100 = 0101000 = bd (again subset of bdeg)
                // if we would have not done '& mask' from above we would have got 0101010 = bdf ('f' was not present in bdeg so its wron)
                subMask = (subMask - 1) & puzzleMask; // get the next substring
            }

            res.add(count);
        }

        return res;
    }
}
```

