solutions.content:
This might be easier to understand than the subset and mask generating code of the other solutions I've seen.
Use itertools.combinations to find all subsets of a puzzle set, and add together the frequency counts.
```
from itertools import combinations
from collections import Counter

class Solution(object):
    def findNumOfValidWords(self, words, puzzles):
        freq = Counter(frozenset(word) for word in words)

        def gen_subsets(puzzle):
            for i in range(1, len(puzzle)+1):
                for comb in combinations(puzzle, i):
                    yield frozenset(comb)

        return [sum(freq[subset]
                    for subset in gen_subsets(puzzle) if puzzle[0] in subset) for puzzle in puzzles]
```

