solutions.content:
It seems that I got TLE in JAVA during the contest because I failed to take advantage of the fixed length of puzzles.

During the contest I got TLE for my first submission, where I just used bitwise operation for up to` (words.length * puzzles.length)` times, and the fixed length of puzzles was only used to rule out those words containing more than 7 different characters.

And it was after reading [this post](https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-valid-words-for-each-puzzle/discuss/371876/Detailed-Explanation-using-Trie-O(word_length-+-100*puzzle_length)) (by Just__a__Visitor) when I realized even `7!` is a constant number which can be much smaller than `words.length` in the worst case, and this condition of fixed puzzle length should really be made good use of. Then I modified the solution so that for each puzzle we only make `2**6` checks, instead of `words.length` checks.

To further explain this idea, if a word is like "aacd", the pattern would be 0000001101, with the three ones from right representing 'a', 'c' and 'd' respectively. And for a puzzle like "abcdefg", we will check each of the sub-patterns containing the first character 'a' and any zero to six characters from `{'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g'}`.

Please forgive me for my ugly usage of both English and Java. And if there are any mistakes in this post please kindly point out so that I won't mislead anyone else.

```
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.List;

class Solution {

    private static int[] masks;
    static {
        masks = new int[26];
        masks[0] = 1;
        for (int i = 1; i < 26; i++)
            masks[i] = masks[i - 1] << 1;
    }

    public List<Integer> findNumOfValidWords(String[] words, String[] puzzles) {

        HashMap<Integer, Integer> wordPattern = new HashMap<>();
        for (String w : words) {
            int pat = getPattern(w);
            if (pat > 0) wordPattern.put(pat, wordPattern.getOrDefault(pat, 0) + 1);
        }

        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();

        for (String puz : puzzles) {
            int cnt = 0;
            ArrayList<Integer> subPatterns = getAllSubPatterns(puz);
            for (int subPat : subPatterns)
                cnt += wordPattern.getOrDefault(subPat, 0);
            ans.add(cnt);
        }
        return ans;
    }

    private ArrayList<Integer> getAllSubPatterns(String s) {
        ArrayList<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < (1 << 6); i++) {
            StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
            sb.append(s.charAt(0));
            for (int k = 0; k < 6; k++)
                if ((i & masks[k]) != 0)
                    sb.append(s.charAt(k + 1));

            ans.add(getPattern(sb.toString()));
        }
        return ans;
    }

    private int getPattern(String s) {
        boolean[] contain = new boolean[26];
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) contain[c - 'a'] = true;
        int ans = 0;
        int cnt = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < 26; i++) {
            if (contain[i]) {
                cnt++;
                ans |= masks[i];
            }
        }
        if (cnt <= 7) return ans;
        return -1;
    }
}
```

